OX^{2}+XD^{2}&=OD^{2}\\
OX^{2}&=OD^{2}-XD^{2}\\
OX&=\sqrt{OD^{2}-XD^{2}}\\
OX&=\sqrt{6^2-4^2}\\
OX&=\sqrt{20}.
